---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';

import governmentHero from '../../assets/government-hero.jpg';
import governmentBuilding from '../../assets/government-building.jpg';
import iaqDashboard from '../../assets/iaq-360-dashboard.png';

/*
 * 1:1 reproduction of the live gsuair.com Government Facilities page: same
 * headings, same copy, same order, same link — nothing added, nothing removed.
 * That includes the section heading that is literally an editor note
 * ("FUNDING....change copy below") and the "FACITIY" typo in the case-study
 * link, both kept at the owner's request.
 */
---

<Base
  title="Government Facilities"
  description="Air and surface purification plus real-time IAQ 360 monitoring for government buildings and correctional facilities. Helps meet OSHA and EPA regulations."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Government Facilities"
    title="PCCD FUNDING PROJECT"
    image={governmentHero}
    imageAlt="Corridor inside a correctional facility"
  />

  <Section tone="tint" title="WHY AIR QUALITY MATTERS IN GOVERNMENT FACILITIES">
    <div class="mt-8 grid items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.4fr_1fr]">
      <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
        <p>
          Poor indoor air quality within government facilities not only has a direct impact on the health of employees
          and visitors, but government facilities must also follow strict health and safety regulations enforced by OSHA
          and the EPA. The higher the occupancy and traffic, the more dust, allergens, and pollutants in the air. Without
          properly purifying the indoor air, contaminants quickly accumulate .
        </p>
        <p>
          Along with that, infrastructure and HVAC systems in older government buildings deteriorate over time, which
          leads to filters not properly circulating clean air. Identified health issues such as Legionnaire's disease,
          asthma, and hypersensitivity pneumonitis have been linked to poor indoor air quality and/or poor ventilation in
          such facilities.
        </p>
      </div>
      <Image
        src={governmentBuilding}
        alt="Exterior of a government office building"
        widths={[400, 700, 1000]}
        sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 26rem, 100vw"
        class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- The live page titles this section "FUNDING....change copy below" — an
       editor note that shipped to production. Reproduced verbatim. -->
  <Section tone="brand" title="FUNDING....change copy below">
    <div class="mt-8 grid items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-brand-100">
        <p>
          GERM SOLUTIONS USA provides the Indoor Air Quality Monitoring System 360. This technology enables building
          administrators to continuously monitor in real-time the air quality within a facility. This proactive approach
          allows for early detection of any potential issues and ensures prompt action can be taken to maintain a healthy
          indoor environment.
        </p>
        <p>
          Aerus indoor air purification products are designed to release molecules that actively target and disable
          COVID-19 and other pathogens present in the air and on surfaces. Integrating these systems into the existing
          infrastructure creates a safer, healthier environment for all who enter the building.
        </p>
        <p>
          At GERM SOLUTIONS USA, we are committed to leveraging this innovative technology to address the issues
          associated with the indoor air quality of government buildings and facilities. The combination of the IAQ 360
          testing service and Aerus indoor air purification system results in a safer and healthier environment for
          employees and visitors as well as meeting OSHA and the EPA regulations.
        </p>
      </div>
      <Image
        src={iaqDashboard}
        alt="IAQ 360 monitoring dashboard showing real-time air quality readings alongside its sensor unit"
        widths={[400, 800, 1400]}
        sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 34rem, 100vw"
        class="rounded-2xl bg-white p-4 shadow-lg"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section tone="tint">
    <div class="text-center">
      <a
        href="/industries/government-facilities/cambria-county"
        class="inline-block font-display text-xl font-bold leading-relaxed tracking-wide text-brand-700 underline underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:text-brand-600 sm:text-2xl text-balance"
      >
        LEHIGH, YORK, CAMBRIA COUNTY PRISON FACITIY SUCCESS STORY....READ MORE
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Base>
